The paper discusses privacy-preserving learning of machine learning models from distributed electronic health records, which falls under the category of privacy and security (cs.CR). The paper also describes a strategy for building machine learning models, which involves feature selection and Bayesian networks learning, indicating that it could also belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
